      <abstract>
        <p>Cationic porphyrins interact strongly with guanine quadruplex DNA (G-quadruplex). We herein report the preparation of a cationic porphyrin bearing quinolinium side arms, 1,1&#x2019;,1&#x2019;&#x2019;,1&#x2019;&#x2019;&#x2019;-[porphyrin-5,10,15,20-tetrayltetrakis(3,1-phenylenemethylene)]tetraquinolinium tetrabromide (<bold><italic>m</italic>Qu</bold>), as a potential G-quadruplex ligand.</p>
      </abstract>
